": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.16848977810511e-17, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"some 44 nations\", \"from\": 232, \"to\": 247}, {\"ngram\": \"the Games\", \"from\": 281, \"to\": 290}, {\"ngram\": \"the VIII Olympiad\", \"from\": 294, \"to\": 311}, {\"ngram\": \"place\", \"from\": 323, \"to\": 328}, {\"ngram\": \"May 4th\", \"from\": 334, \"to\": 341}, {\"ngram\": \"July 27th\", \"from\": 345, \"to\": 354}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Germany was banned from taking part, as it had been in 1920.\", \"from\": 356, \"to\": 416, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 356, \"end\": 363, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Germany_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9999996289357802, \"rank\": 2.6803702777532083e-07, \"text\": \"Germany\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Germany_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Germany_national_football_team\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"part\", \"from\": 387, \"to\": 391}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In total, 3,089 athletes competed in 126 events in 17 different sports.\", \"from\": 417, \"to\": 488, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"total\", \"from\": 420, \"to\": 425}, {\"ngram\": \"3,089 athletes\", \"from\": 427, \"to\": 441}, {\"ngram\": \"126 events\", \"from\": 454, \"to\": 464}, {\"ngram\": \"17 different sports\", \"from\": 468, \"to\": 487}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Ireland's 48 athletes competed in seven different events including the high jump, boxing and the shot put, javelin, water polo, football and tennis.\", \"from\": 489, \"to\": 637, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 489, \"end\": 496, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"score\": 0.9999999163387692, \"rank\": 8.341394824167468e-08, \"text\": \"Ireland\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"seven different events\", \"from\": 523, \"to\": 545}, {\"ngram\": \"the high jump\", \"from\": 556, \"to\": 569}, {\"ngram\": \"boxing\", \"from\": 571, \"to\": 577}, {\"ngram\": \"the shot\", \"from\": 582, \"to\": 590}, {\"ngram\": \"javelin\", \"from\": 596, \"to\": 603}, {\"ngram\": \"water polo\", \"from\": 605, \"to\": 615}, {\"ngram\": \"football\", \"from\": 617, \"to\": 625}, {\"ngram\": \"tennis\", \"from\": 630, \"to\": 636}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Ireland's participation at the 1924 Olympics was a powerful statement of its newfound independence.\", \"from\": 639, \"to\": 738, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 639, \"end\": 646, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"score\": 0.9999999163387692, \"rank\": 8.341394824167468e-08, \"text\": \"Ireland\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the 1924 Olympics\", \"from\": 666, \"to\": 683}, {\"ngram\": \"a powerful statement\", \"from\": 688, \"to\": 708}, {\"ngram\": \"its newfound independence\", \"from\": 712, \"to\": 737}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Much of the work to make Ireland eligible to compete at the 1924 Games as an independent nation was down toJ.J.\", \"from\": 739, \"to\": 850, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 764, \"end\": 771, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"score\": 0.9999999163387692, \"rank\": 8.341394824167468e-08, \"text\": \"Ireland\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the work\", \"from\": 747, \"to\": 755}, {\"ngram\": \"the 1924 Games\", \"from\": 795, \"to\": 809}, {\"ngram\": \"an independent nation\", \"from\": 813, \"to\": 834}, {\"ngram\": \"toJ.J.\", \"from\": 844, \"to\": 850}]}, {\"sentence\": \"(John James) Keane.\", \"from\": 851, \"to\": 870, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 852, \"end\": 862, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/John_E._James\", \"score\": 0.9999975997158502, \"rank\": 1.0866293030761497e-06, \"text\": \"John James\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/John_E._James\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/John_E._James\"}], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He founded theIrish Olympic Councilin the early 1920s and became its first president.\", \"from\": 871, \"to\": 956, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"theIrish Olympic Councilin\", \"from\": 882, \"to\": 908}, {\"ngram\": \"its first president\", \"from\": 936, \"to\": 955}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He lobbied the governing body of the Olympics, theInternational Olympic Committee, and its president,Baron Pierre de Coubertin, to have Ireland admitted.\", \"from\": 957, \"to\": 1110, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1064, \"end\": 1083, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pierre_de_Coubertin\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Pierre de Coubertin\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pierre_de_Coubertin\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pierre_de_Coubertin\"}, {\"begin\": 1093, \"end\": 1100, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"score\": 0.9999999163387692, \"rank\": 8.341394824167468e-08, \"text\": \"Ireland\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the governing body\", \"from\": 968, \"to\": 986}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 990, \"to\": 1002}, {\"ngram\": \"theInternational Olympic Committee\", \"from\": 1004, \"to\": 1038}, {\"ngram\": \"its president\", \"from\": 1044, \"to\": 1057}]}, {\"sentence\": \"His hard work paid off and Ireland was allowed to compete with the other nations of the world in what is perhaps the largest and most famous sporting contest in the world.\", \"from\": 1111, \"to\": 1282, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1138, \"end\": 1145, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"score\": 0.9999999163387692, \"rank\": 8.341394824167468e-08, \"text\": \"Ireland\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"His hard work\", \"from\": 1111, \"to\": 1124}, {\"ngram\": \"the other nations\", \"from\": 1174, \"to\": 1191}, {\"ngram\": \"the world\", \"from\": 1195, \"to\": 1204}, {\"ngram\": \"the largest and most famous sporting contest\", \"from\": 1224, \"to\": 1268}, {\"ngram\": \"the world\", \"from\": 1272, \"to\": 1281}]}, {\"sentence\": \"From Path\\u00e9, coverage of the opening ceremony of the 1924 Olympic Games Ireland marched in 25th position in the opening ceremony which took place at theStade Olympique de Colombeson July 5th 1924.\", \"from\": 1286, \"to\": 1482, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1291, \"end\": 1296, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Path\\u00e9\", \"score\": 0.9705077135553523, \"rank\": 0.019446089512071708, \"text\": \"Path\\u00e9\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Path\\u00e9\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Path\\u00e9\"}, {\"begin\": 1358, \"end\": 1365, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"score\": 0.9999999163387692, \"rank\": 8.341394824167468e-08, \"text\": \"Ireland\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"coverage\", \"from\": 1298, \"to\": 1306}, {\"ngram\": \"the opening ceremony\", \"from\": 1310, \"to\": 1330}, {\"ngram\": \"25th position\", \"from\": 1376, \"to\": 1389}, {\"ngram\": \"the opening ceremony\", \"from\": 1393, \"to\": 1413}, {\"ngram\": \"place\", \"from\": 1425, \"to\": 1430}, {\"ngram\": \"theStade Olympique de Colombeson\", \"from\": 1434, \"to\": 1466}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They marched behind the tricolour and this proved to be controversial for some nations: the Philippines wereannoyedthat they had to parade behind their flag and that of the United States as it was occupied by the US at the time.\", \"from\": 1483, \"to\": 1711, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1575, \"end\": 1586, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philippines\", \"score\": 0.9993145115811579, \"rank\": 0.000555568864477238, \"text\": \"Philippines\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philippines\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philippines\"}, {\"begin\": 1656, \"end\": 1669, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_women's_national_soccer_team\", \"score\": 0.9968804678723148, \"rank\": 0.0017652015474723798, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_women's_national_soccer_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_women's_national_soccer_team\"}, {\"begin\": 1696, \"end\": 1698, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9972736923908242, \"rank\": 0.002732049188478922, \"text\": \"US\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the tricolour\", \"from\": 1503, \"to\": 1516}, {\"ngram\": \"some nations\", \"from\": 1557, \"to\": 1569}, {\"ngram\": \"wereannoyedthat\", \"from\": 1587, \"to\": 1602}, {\"ngram\": \"their flag\", \"from\": 1629, \"to\": 1639}, {\"ngram\": \"the time\", \"from\": 1702, \"to\": 1710}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Ireland's flag bearer was the world champion weight throwerJohn O'Grady.\", \"from\": 1713, \"to\": 1785, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1713, \"end\": 1720, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"score\": 0.9999999163387692, \"rank\": 8.341394824167468e-08, \"text\": \"Ireland\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\"}, {\"begin\": 1777, \"end\": 1784, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stuart_O'Grady\", \"score\": 0.9999999998940439, \"rank\": 1.0599752151457274e-10, \"text\": \"O'Grady\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stuart_O'Grady\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stuart_O'Grady\"}], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"As well as a flag to show spectators which team was being led out, a banner with the country's name was also displayed.\", \"from\": 1786, \"to\": 1905, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"spectators\", \"from\": 1812, \"to\": 1822}, {\"ngram\": \"which team\", \"from\": 1823, \"to\": 1833}, {\"ngram\": \"a banner\", \"from\": 1853, \"to\": 1861}, {\"ngram\": \"the country's name\", \"from\": 1867, \"to\": 1885}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In Ireland's case, the banner read 'Ireland' which was not technically correct as the island had been partitioned into the Free State and Northern Ireland.\", \"from\": 1906, \"to\": 2061, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1909, \"end\": 1916, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"score\": 0.9999999163387692, \"rank\": 8.341394824167468e-08, \"text\": \"Ireland\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\"}, {\"begin\": 194